snippet.textDisplay:
Even if you don't want to be more environmentally friendly there are many other pros about electric cars. You don't have to waste time going to fuel stations when you just want to go home or when you're late for work. They are less noisy. They're not constantly vibrating because of a running engine. There are way less engine parts, so it is way more reliable. You're not having those annoying gear shifts. They have instant torque and are therefore very responsive and quick. Less fuel costs. And if you have solar panels you can directly charge your car for free* while it is sitting at home unused. And I feel like there are way more reasons I've forgot to mention.
Even if global warming wasn't a huge threat to our society I'd still want an electric car because of all these benefits. And buying electric only makes development of electric cars go faster, and therefore future electric cars will be even better.
